One portion of this dish contains approximately 79g of protein, 73g of fat, and a total of 2061 calories. 1 person has made this recipe and would make it again. A mixture of & healthy, spring, sunday lunch, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so yummy. To use up the mixed vegetables you could follow this main course with the Pumpkin Pie Dessert as a dessert. It is perfect for Autumn. It is brought to you by BBC Good Food.
